The paper proposes a new matrix factorization model and algorithm that combines nonnegative matrix factorization (NMF) and subtropical matrix factorization (SMF). As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new matrix factorization model and algorithm, which are relevant to machine learning. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for matrix factorization, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms. 

cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses a model that involves latent parameters, which is relevant to information theory. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper does not explicitly discuss social or information networks, but the proposed model and algorithm could be applied to network data. 

cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a new algorithm for matrix factorization, which is relevant to numerical analysis.
